description: A majestic native oak tree known for its strong wood and beautiful fall foliage. Provides excellent shade and supports wildlife.
plantingCareInfo: Plant in well-draining soil with full sun to partial shade. Water regularly during first year. Prune in late winter.

description: Famous for its spectacular fall colors and maple syrup production. A long-lived tree that provides excellent shade.
plantingCareInfo: Prefers moist, well-drained soil and partial shade. Avoid salt exposure. Water during dry periods.

description: Beautiful spring-flowering tree with heart-shaped leaves and pink-purple flowers that bloom before the leaves emerge.
plantingCareInfo: Thrives in partial shade to full sun. Tolerates various soil types. Drought tolerant once established.

description: A fast-growing native conifer with soft, blue-green needles. Excellent for windbreaks and year-round privacy.
plantingCareInfo: Plant in well-drained, slightly acidic soil. Full sun to partial shade. Water regularly during establishment.

description: Stunning native tree with showy white or pink spring flowers and brilliant red fall foliage. Perfect understory tree.
plantingCareInfo: Prefers partial shade and moist, well-drained soil. Mulch to keep roots cool. Avoid wet feet.

description: Adaptable native maple with brilliant red fall color. Fast-growing and tolerates various soil conditions.
plantingCareInfo: Very adaptable to soil conditions. Prefers moist soil but tolerates drought. Full sun to partial shade.

description: Distinctive white bark makes this native birch a year-round focal point. Yellow fall foliage adds seasonal interest.
plantingCareInfo: Prefers cool, moist soil and partial shade. Keep roots cool with mulch. Avoid compacted soil.

description: Classic American shade tree with graceful arching branches. Disease-resistant varieties available for urban landscapes.
plantingCareInfo: Adaptable to various soils. Full sun preferred. Regular watering during establishment. Prune in winter.

description: Deciduous conifer with beautiful feathery foliage that turns bronze in fall. Excellent for wet sites and unique garden features.
plantingCareInfo: Thrives in wet to moist soil but adapts to well-drained sites. Full sun preferred. Very low maintenance.

description: Tall native tree with distinctive tulip-shaped flowers and unique four-lobed leaves. Fast-growing shade tree.
plantingCareInfo: Prefers deep, moist, well-drained soil. Full sun to partial shade. Space adequately for mature size.
